race.comment: WYNDINTHEWILLOWS (8) peaks and has been nudged out at her last two over a mile. She's won over a middle distance in Victoria, so the step up in trip should hold no fears. Tough to beat. TIDEFORD (2) capped strong form with a CL1 win at Launceston over this distance. He is free running and draws well. Is on the improve and will be hard to peg back. CARNOTAURUS (10) was on-pace beaten 2L by the above, and she improved again. Always puts in and is well in the mix. WHOLESOME (7) has needed the two runs for the new stable and improved last time. Has placed 2/2 at this distance and the top hoop rides. Can make the finish with average luck from the wide gate. INFRINGEMENT (3) just missed at Hobart over a mile and looks to be finally hitting his straps.
